HEADWORD: Tonsured
<hw>Ton"sured</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having the tonsure;
shaven; shorn; clipped; hence, bald.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>tonsured</qex> head in middle age forlorn.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tontine</ent>⟦br⟧
